{{Infobox film | name = Amateur | image = Amateur (2018 film).png | director = Ryan Koo |producer = {{plainlist| * [[Jason Michael Berman]] * [[Mark Moran (producer)|Mark Moran]] * [[Chip Hourihan]] }} | writer = Ryan Koo | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Michael Rainey Jr.]] }} |music = BC Smith |cinematography = Gregory J. Wilson |editing = Jeff Wishengrad | production companies = {{Plainlist| * Mandalay Pictures * [[Netflix]] }} | distributor = Netflix | released = {{Film date|2018|4|06|United States}} | runtime = 96 minutes | country = United States | language = English }}
'''''Amateur''''' is a 2018 American sports drama about a young basketball future star struggling with his personal life in pursuit of his dream. The film was released in the United States on April 6, 2018 on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://filmmakermagazine.com/105039-trailer-watch-ryan-koos-amateur/ |title=Trailer Watch: Ryan Koo’s Amateur |first=Scott |last=Macaulay |date=19 March 2018 |publisher=[[Filmmaker magazine]] |access-date=28 April 2018}}</ref>
==Synopsis== 14-year-old basketball phenom Terron Forte has to navigate the under-the-table world of amateur basketball when he is recruited to an elite NCAA prep school.
==Cast== * [[Michael Rainey Jr.]] as Terron Forte * Tekola Cornetet as Stevion * Walter Anaruk as Coach Nguyen * [[Sharon Leal]] as Nia, Terron's mother * [[Brian J. White]] as Vince, Terron's father * Ketrick Copeland as Byron * [[Josh Charles]] as Coach Gaines * [[Corey Parker Robinson]] as Coach Curtis * James Siakam as Olembe * Stefan Frank as Petrus * Ashlee Brian as Anton
==Production== A crowd-funding project for the film, then known as ''Manchild'', was started in 2011 by director Ryan Koo.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/ryanbkoo/man-child-feature-film |title=AMATEUR - Feature Film (formerly MANCHILD) |last=Koo |first=Ryan |website=kickstarter.com |access-date=28 April 2018}}</ref> In 2013, a short prequel to ''Manchild'' was released under the name ''Amateur''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.slamonline.com/blogs/directing-traffic/amateur-ryan-koos-prequel-to-manchild/ |title=Amateur: Ryan Koo’s Prequel to Manchild |first=Duane |last=Watson |date=13 September 2013 |publisher=[[Slam (magazine)|Slam]] |access-date=28 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://filmmakermagazine.com/68806-ryan-koo-on-amateur-feature-fundraising-and-the-kickstarter-long-game/ |title=Ryan Koo on Amateur, Feature Fundraising, and the Kickstarter Long Game |first=Scott |last=Macaulay |date=17 April 2013 |publisher=[[Filmmaker magazine]] |access-date=28 April 2018}}</ref> In November 2014, the name of the film was changed to its release title ''Amateur''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/ryanbkoo/man-child-feature-film/posts/1058326 |title=We've changed our title to 'Amateur' — and you're invited to a Sundance Reading! |last=Koo |first=Ryan |date=20 November 2014 |website=kickstarter.com |access-date=28 April 2018}}</ref> In January 2016, it was announced that [[Netflix]] had picked up the rights to ''Amateur'' to finance and distribute the film.<ref>[http://deadline.com/2016/01/netflix-expands-global-indie-strategy-with-slate-of-new-features-sundance-1201686623/ Netflix Expands Global Indie Strategy With Slate Of New Features]</ref><ref>[https://variety.com/2016/film/news/netflix-movies-amateur-clinical-1201684577/ Netflix Expands Movie Slate With Five Titles]</ref>
