{{infobox country at games | NPC = CPV | NPCname = Comité Caboverdeano Desp. Para Deficientes | games = Paralympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 1 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Cape Verde|competition=Summer Paralympics|begin_year=2004|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Cape Verde]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] début at the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Athens]], with two competitors in track and field, and one in powerlifting. The country sent a single athlete ([[Artimiza Sequeira]]) to the [[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Games]], to compete in the women's shot put, discus and javelin.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=CPV&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Cape Verde at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
In Rio de Janeiro 2016, sprinter Gracelino Barbosa won Cape Verde's first Paralympic medal, a bronze in the Men's 400m T20.
Cape Verde has never taken part in the [[Winter Paralympics]].<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=CPV&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Cape Verde at the Paralympics], International Paralympic Committee</ref>
==See also== * [[Cape Verde at the Olympics]]
