{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Chongqing Olympic Sports Center | location=[[Chongqing]], China | image = [[File:ChongqingOlympicStadium bird's eyes view.png|250px]] | caption = [[Bird's-eye view]] | coordinates = {{Coord|29.525246|N|106.506282|E|format=dms|type:landmark_scale:5000_region:CN-50|display=it}} | opened=2004 | owner= Municipality of Chongqing | operator = Chongqing Sports Bureau | tenants=[[Chongqing Lifan F.C.]] | seating_capacity=58,680 }} The '''Chongqing Olympic Sports Center''' ({{zh|s=重庆奥林匹克体育中心 |t=重慶奧林匹克體育中心}}) is a sports venue featuring a 58,680-seat [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Chongqing]], China.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://plus.google.com/113730721859413094186/about?gl=uk&hl=en | title=Chongqing Olympic Sports Center | publisher=[[Google+]] | accessdate=20 August 2014 }}</ref>
The sports center is the home stadium of [[Chongqing Lifan F.C.]] of [[Chinese Football Association Super League]]. It was built in 2004.
The stadium is also a popular venue for concerts. [[Mariah Carey]] began her [[The Elusive Chanteuse Show]] tour in China at the stadium on October 15, 2014.
