{{use dmy dates|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox sportsperson | name = Fernando Arlete | birth_name = | image = | caption = | nationality = Bissau-Guinean | sport = Middle-distance running | event = 800 metres | club = | collegeteam = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1968|10|11|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | height = | weight = }}
'''Fernando Arlete''' (born 11 October 1968) is a Bissau-Guinean [[middle-distance running|middle-distance runner]]. He competed in the [[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's 800 metres|men's 800 metres]] at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]].<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ar/fernando-arlete-1.html |title=Fernando Arlete Olympic Results |accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>
