{{DEFAULTSORT:Macron (Sportswear)}} [[Category:Sportswear brands]] [[Category:Clothing brands of Italy]] [[Category:Clothing companies of Italy]] [[Category:Sporting goods manufacturers of Italy]] [[Category:Companies based in Emilia-Romagna]] [[Category:Province of Bologna]] [[Category:Privately held companies of Italy]] [[Category:Italian companies established in 1971]] [[Category:Italian brands]] [[Category:Clothing companies established in 1971]]

This is a list of countries according to the best position achieved by athletes of these nations at [[List of hockey world championships|major world tournaments]] in [[roller hockey]]. The [[:Category:Variations of hockey|variations of hockey]] included here are [[roller hockey (quad)|quad]] (also known as rink hockey) and [[roller in-line hockey|inline hockey]]. Aside from the best results achieved at the [[world championships]] for each variation, also included are results from the [[World Games]] and the [[World Roller Games]]. Medals earned by athletes from defunct [[National Olympic Committee|NOCs]] or historical teams have been merged with the results achieved by their immediate [[succession of states|successor states]], as follows: [[Czech Republic]] inherits medals from [[Czechoslovakia]] and [[Germany]] inherits medals from [[West Germany]]. Medals earned by teams from [[England]] are merged with results from [[Great Britain]]. Results achieved in youth, junior or U20 events were not considered for the making of this table, neither were [[parasports|para]] adaptations of hockey ([[power hockey]]). == Results == {| class="wikitable" style="margin-top:0em; text-align:center; font-size:100%;" |+ '''Last updated after the [[2017 World Roller Games]]''' ! rowspan="2" colspan="2" style="background: #f2f2ce;" | ! colspan="4" style="background: #f2f2ce;" | [[Roller hockey (quad)|Quad hockey]]&nbsp;<small>([[Fédération Internationale de Roller Sports|FIRS]])</small> ! colspan="6" style="background: #f2f2ce;" | [[Roller in-line&nbsp;hockey]]&nbsp;<small>([[Fédération Internationale de Roller Sports|FIRS]] and [[International Ice Hockey Federation|IIHF]])</small> |- ! colspan="2" style="background: #f2f2ce;" | [[FIRS Roller Hockey World Cup|World&nbsp;Cup]] ! colspan="1" style="background: #f2f2ce;" | [[Roller hockey at the World Games|World&nbsp;Games]] ! colspan="1" style="background: #f2f2ce;" | [[World Roller Games|Roller&nbsp;Games]] ! colspan="3" style="backgrou