{{Infobox venue | name = McConnell Arena | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = [[File:Arena McConnell 01.jpg|275px]] | caption = | fullname = | former_names = McConnell Winter Arena | location = 3883 [[University Street]], [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|45.511971|-73.582692|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1956<!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | renovated = 2000<ref name="redmen">{{cite web|url=http://www.redmenhockey.com/recruiting/recruiting.shtml|title=Recruiting|work=|publisher=The unofficial website of [[McGill Redmen]] hockey|accessdate=22 December 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091230084533/http://www.redmenhockey.com/recruiting/recruiting.shtml|archivedate=30 December 2009|df=}}</ref> | expanded = 2004<ref name="advertising">{{cite web|url=http://www.redmenhockey.com/McConnell_Arena_dasher_board_ads-2011-2012.pdf|title=McGill University's McConnell Arena Dasher Board Advertising|work=[[McGill Redmen]]|publisher=[[McGill University]]|accessdate=21 August 2012}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[McGill University]] | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 1,600<ref name="advertising" /> | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[McGill Redmen]], [[McGill Martlets]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''McConnell Arena''' is an [[ice hockey]] [[arena]] located on the corner of [[Pine Avenue]] and [[Park Avenue (Montreal)|Park Avenue]] in [[Montreal|Montreal, Quebec]], Canada. The arena is owned and operated by [[McGill University]], and is the home to the [[McGill Redmen]] men's and [[McGill Martlets women's ice hockey]] teams. The ice surface is the standard North American size, 61 metres (200 feet) long by 26 metres (85&nbsp;feet) wide.
Since an expansion in 2004, the arena has a capacity of 1,600 people.<ref name="redmen"/>
==History== McConnell Arena was originally built in 1956 due to a donation by [[John Wilson McConnell]], a Canadian businessman, newspaper publisher, humanitarian, philanthropist and senior governor of McGill University.<ref name="redmen"/> It was renovated in 2000 at a cost of $4 million.<ref name="redmen"/>
<gallery> Image:McConnell Arena-02.jpg|The scoreboard at the McConnell Arena. Image:Playoff Brampton-Montreal 002.jpg|Ice rink of McConnell Arena </gallery>
