{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''Yap Sports Complex''' is located in Abay, Gagil, [[Yap State, Federated States of Micronesia]]. It is the national [[stadium]] and the home of Yap sporting events. The stadium's capacity is around 2,000, and it was built in 2001—in time for the 3rd FSM Games.In 2018, It was renovated and extended in time for the 9th [[Micronesian Games]] hosted by [[Yap State]] for the very first time.

