'''Yards After Catch (YAC)''' is the term used in [[American football]] for the distance gained by a receiver after catching a pass.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.washingtonpost.com/fb/glossary.asp|title=Washington Post-NFL Football Glossary| accessdate=2009-01-17|publisher=washingtonpost.com}}</ref> Specifically, it is the forward yardage gained from the spot of the [[Reception (American football)|reception]] until the receiver is downed, runs out of bounds, scores, or loses the ball.

