'''Yogan Santos''' (born 15 January 1985) is a [[Gibraltarian people|Gibraltarian]] [[Association football|footballer]] who last played for [[Gibraltar Premier Division]] side [[Manchester 62 F.C.|Manchester 62]] and the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] national team, where he plays as a [[Defender (association football)|Defender]].
==International career==
Santos was first called up to the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar senior team]] in February 2014 for [[exhibition match|friendlies]] against [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] and [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]] on 1 and 5 March 2014.<ref name="GFA reveals squads">{{cite web|title=GFA reveals squads for upcoming friendlies|url=http://www.gbc.gi/news/3190/gfa-reveals-squads-for-upcoming-friendlies|publisher=GBC|accessdate=4 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="Faroe Islands and Estonia">{{cite web|title=Squad for Faroe Islands and Estonia friendlies announced|url=http://footballgibraltar.wordpress.com/2014/02/11/squad-for-faroe-islands-and-estonia-friendlies-announced/|publisher=footballgibraltar.wordpress.com|accessdate=4 March 2014}}</ref> He made his international début with Gibraltar on 1 March 2014 in a 4-1 home loss with the [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]].<ref name="gib debut">{{cite news|title=Gibraltar crash back down to earth with heavy Faroe Islands loss|url=http://nonfifafootball.blogspot.co.uk/2014/03/the-reality-of-uefa-international.html|accessdate=4 March 2014|date=1 March 2014}}</ref> His second appearance came a 2-0 home loss to [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]] on 5 March 2014. Playing at [[Left Back]] in both games
On 14 November 2014, he scored an [[own goal]] in Gibraltar's 4–0 defeat to [[Germany national football team|Germany]].
